description: R U a new Douglass Residential College student or considering adding Douglass to your Rutgers experience? Meet current and new Douglass students, get helpful info about Douglass and Rutgers, connect with Douglass staff over snacks and get your first Douglass swag! Douglass is an empowering, close-knit community within Rutgers that enhances the college experience for students of all majors by adding a feminist lens to your education. Douglass welcomes all undergraduate students, commuters and students living on campus. Through the Douglass curriculum you are inspired to examine inequality, center women’s lived experience, and embolden women’s leadership. By adding Douglass you are sure to leave Rutgers with a robust resume full of the academic, professional, and co-curricular experiences that will make you a competitive candidate in the job market, graduate school application process, or any other endeavor you choose to pursue. **This event is for newly enrolled Douglass students who added Douglass after the start of the Fall '24 semester or for the current Spring '25 semester, or anyone considering adding Douglass to their RU experience**
location: Kathleen W. Ludgwig Building, Schonberg Room
name: Douglass New Student Facts & Snacks
organizationName: Enrollment, Scholarship, Housing and Commuter Engagement at Douglass Residential College at Douglass Residential College - DRC

description: AUG is holding its annual Genetics Faculty Meet and Greet on Friday, January 24th, 2025 at 4:00 PM(exact time is subject to change) in the Life Sciences Building Atrium on Busch!
